related_questions.question: Is beef based on a true story?
related_questions.snippet: 'Beef' is based on a real road rage incident Showrunner Lee Sung Jin tells TODAY.com that he was inspired to create the show based on his own road rage experience. He says it was a "typical" interaction — "honking, cursing at me and then drove off." "For some reason," Lee decided to follow the other driver.

related_questions.question: What is the point of beef on Netflix?
related_questions.snippet: Beef follows the aftermath of a road rage accident between two strangers: Danny Cho, a troubled contractor, and Amy Lau, a self-made business owner. Over the 10-episode first season, their incident escalates into a full-on feud between the pair, ultimately consuming their relationships and lives.

related_questions.question: Is beef a Korean show?
related_questions.snippet: Beef is an American comedy-drama television miniseries created by Korean-American director Lee Sung Jin for Netflix. It stars Steven Yeun and Ali Wong as Danny Cho and Amy Lau, respectively; two strangers whose involvement in a road rage incident escalates into a prolonged feud.
